            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "So here's the solution I've come to, which is working, pending a little more experimentation before I submit a PR.\n\nRelease events are notated as R-\n\nPress events are notated as P- with an additional event firing alongside the actual key event itself.\n\nRepeat events are not given any special treatment.\n\nThe theory here is that this enables plugin developers to unbind the button they wish to work with and to use the press and release events, what we really don't want is to impact the existing behaviour and functionality of the key.\n\nThis to my mind is a big part of why the original suggestion exclusively added release bindings. It's better to make plugin developers using this functionality need to tinker a bit than it is to break things.",
