            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">Release events are notated as R-\n>\n>Press events are notated as P- with an additional event firing alongside the actual key event itself.\n\nI'm not sure if we should re-use the same syntax as modifiers, since these events aren't modifiers like Alt or Ctrl. They're a different kind of thing completely and notating them as if they were modifiers is misleading.\n\nWhat about prefixing with `R:` or `P:` instead (i.e. with a colon). So a press event mapping would use e.g. `<P:C-K>` and a release event `<R:C-K>`",
